HEADWORD: Bioplasm
<hw>Bi"o*plasm</hw> <pr>(b⟦imac⟧"⟦osl⟧*pl⟦acr⟧z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>bi`os</grk> life + <grk>pla`sma</grk> form, mold, fr.
<grk>pla`ssein</grk> to mold.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A name
suggested by Dr. Beale for the germinal matter supposed to be essential
to the functions of all living beings; the material through which every
form of life manifests itself; unaltered protoplasm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

